<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\12_oldsong\12_cv_sky_dragon</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>27</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>As you reach the summit of the mountain, a gust of wind stirs the air. You hear a noise like the snapping of sails, and the sky is briefly blotted out. A dragon lands before you, shaking the ground beneath your feet.

It draws itself up to its full height and spreads its wings, barring your passage. Its neck, its back, and the ridge of its spine are covered with magnificent plumage.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You have young here?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack] "Not if I kill you both."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>The dragon slowly lowers its wings, watching you carefully. It grunts and lowers itself onto all fours. 

"So be it. Go, then, and with my thanks."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>Heat from the beast's roar sears your face. It lashes in a flurry of scales and feathers.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Vermin invading my nest. Threatening my hatchling." It snorts a stream of sulfurous vapor. "You shall feed my young."

A small wurm crouches in a corner of the temple behind the dragon.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"This is a temple dedicated to a goddess, not your hatchery."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've been sent to get you to leave so that Hylea's worshipers may return."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>The beast snarls, smoke jetting from its nostrils. "I will protect my last hatchling to the death. And that death will be yours, rodent."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hylea is the goddess of motherhood, actually."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You should find a different place to make your nest."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>A low rumble issues from the dragon's throat, and it bristles its feathered crest. "And of the sky and all winged creatures." Tendrils of smoke rise from between its teeth. "Even my kind know of her."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Then you should respect her temple and leave."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Is that why you came here?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>It flicks the tip of its feathered tail. "I came to care for my remaining hatchling. My kind requires territory. Few places are safe for our young."

The dragon runs a forked tongue over teeth the size of short swords. A chunk of flesh is lodged between two of its cuspids. 

"This is a lesson that cost me the rest of my brood."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>The dragon spares you a cautious glance before returning its attention to the wurm.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>Blood boils out of the dragon's nostrils. It coughs sickly, black clouds of smoke. "Please." Its voice is little more than a sizzling hiss. "You have won. Let me use the last of my strength to carry my child somewhere - anywhere - before I die. Let me give my young a chance."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Then you should stay. Raising your offspring here would honor Hylea."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You and your offspring will kill many if you stay. You have to leave."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Very well. Go."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I can't allow that."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>Wheezing smoke, the dragon clutches its hatchling and spreads its torn wings. It launches itself into a careening trajectory, skimming the tops of trees as it disappears in the distance.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>The dragon roars desperately and renews its attack.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack] "Too bad I have to kill you both."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Be careful, Watcher. Her mind is on edge... not with hunger, but with fear.

"There is little more dangerous than a mother defending her offspring..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Grieving Mother's eyes are warm, approving. "Truly, you are full of surprises... and rare insights."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>It hisses at you, and while the sound is unlike any language you've ever heard, the beast's meaning is utterly clear.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>